Trade data

Source: R/trades.R
trades.Rd

`trades` returns information regarding individual trades that have taken place on the exchange for the given symbol / time frame.

trades(
  symbol = "XBT",
  filter = NULL,
  columns = NULL,
  count = 1000,
  start = NULL,
  reverse = "true",
  startTime = NULL,
  endTime = NULL
)

Arguments

symbol

Instrument symbol. You can also send a timeframe, e.g. XBT:quarterly
filter

Generic table filter. Send JSON key/value pairs, such as "'key':'value'".
columns

Array of column names to fetch. If omitted, will return all columns.
count

Number of results to fetch. Maximum of 1000 (the default) per request.
start

Starting point for results.
reverse

If true, will sort results newest first (default = "true").
startTime

Starting date filter for results.
endTime

Ending date filter for results.

Value

`trades` returns a data.frame containing information for executed trades for the given arguments.

Details

By default, `trades` will return the most recent trade data first. This option can be change by setting `reverse` to "false"
